task.summary: removed the Domain class and replaced all references with the ProteinFeatureWithLocation class
added storing strategy framework and a naive implementation

---------- clean up --------------
removed the (empty) CPDTProtein class, all CPDT output will be kept in the heavy Protein class
removed the obsolete getProteinAccession method from the PepshellProtein class and refactored all references to it with more sensible ones
added javadoc to the Experiment,PepshellProtein,ProteinInterface and FlyWeightProtein class
changed the protein class to pepshellprotein and slimmed down the ProteinInterface class
added a lot more generics everywhere to aid with making the code more flexible
removed the das parser part, as the servers are shutting down
---------- new features --------------
added the ability to add storage managers which can utilise different storage strategies to Pepshell, this allows for deep storage and unicity of the objects being stored, it also ensures that all data presented is uniform, for the moment only proteins have received this treatment
added the flyweightprotein class to alleviate the memory pressure redundant protein data has, this flyweight communicates with the storage manager for all non identifier and non peptide data
changed the DbDAO class with the changes to the ProteinInterface class, still need to refactor to flyweights
added flyweights to the file parsing,
started going through the flow of the program and switch out the PepshellProtein class with the fly weight where possible
added more generics to the storage manager and strategy classes so it is easier to expand upon this
